[ANALYSIS]
The experiment with the CNN architecture achieved a reasonable performance, as indicated by an F1 score of 0.7103 and accuracy of 0.7387. The use of multiple kernel sizes (3, 4, and 5) suggests that the model was able to capture features at different scales within the input data effectively. However, the relatively low number of epochs (3) might have limited the model's ability to fully converge on optimal weights, potentially leading to underfitting. For the next run, increasing the number of epochs could help improve performance by allowing the model more time to learn from the training data. Additionally, experimenting with different learning rates or adjusting the dropout rate might further enhance the model's generalization capabilities.